MOROCCO 🇲🇦 Dispatch from Astoria, Queens: With its bold color scheme and easy to digest chopping block name, Halal Sandwich Shop was one of the last places on Steinway I wanted to explore. Somehow it just gave off too much of a chain fast food vibe. Using it as a quick place to grab a sandwich to take into a nearby hookah bar back during the World Cup and surprised by the impressive offering, I've since been back a few times to try different things. After exploring a good portion of the menu, it is hard not to come back to those delicious Moroccan spicy tuna sandwiches known as poccadios (written poccadillo on the menu here).
Fri specials include a lamb shank (or beef) cous cous w veggies - a huge portion that also comes w bread on the side. Go early cause it's a lunch time crowd that orders all of it quite early.

Not just sandwiches but full Lamb and Beef shanks with rice and other items! Good food at reasonable prices however service is non-existent, which was expected, and seating is sparse. Everything tasted better than expected and I'll visit again. Seemed like a hole in the wall Mediterranean in a very lively area of Steinway, Astoria where competition for Mediterranean is very high. Recommend you at least give their food a try.

Walking around Astoria looking for a shawarma shop we stopped here as the other great shawrma spot was under renovation.  Place had a little jam outside as there were a bunch of people ordering togo and waiting. The sitting area inside is more or less like a quick bite stool and table by the wall as the kitchen takes most of the space as it is needed with all the good stuff they have on the menu.  Looking through the kitchen you can see all the great kebabs ready to be cooked and all the great lamb, beef and veggie broth trays.  We started off by ordering a Chicken kebab , Falafel and kofta sandwiches, also beef and lamb broth platters with a large side order of french fries.  Now the taste...... what can i say it just was amazing ...rightly cooked and the orders jsut came out all at same time rather than one at a time so we could all enjoy are food. Party of 5 killed a lot of food and we wanted more.  Had a nice discussion with the  owners who are Moroccan and gave us a good intro of their food which they said they order fresh meat everyday and marinate it with the basic ingredients ever. Food was right and the way the kitchen worked was every more of a jaw dropper with all the traffic in the store.  Do visit if you are in town as you cannot go wrong.
